If set to FALSE, foxBMS does not check for the presence of a current sensor. If set to TRUE, foxBMS checks for the presence of a current sensor. If sensor stops responding during runtime, an error is raised
If set to FALSE, foxBMS does not check CAN timing. If set to TRUE, foxBMS checks CAN timing. A valid request must come every 100ms, within the 95-150ms window.
If set to TRUE, balancing is deactivated completely. If set to FALSE, foxBMS checks when balancing must be done and activates it accordingly.
